  "label": "Cinderwall Sleep Niche",
  "description": "Cinderwall Sleep Niche forms a narrow, gasketed chamber set behind a pressure-tight interior door, its walls clad in soot-darkened insulation panels to blunt storm-cold and vox bleed. A recessed bunk-frame and lockable storage voids are built directly into the slagcrete ribs, their edges chipped and polished by constant use. Sealed shutter slats over a slit window admit bruise-colored auroral light in thin bands that stain the plascrete floor violet. The air carries a persistent mineral dryness, and ash residue gathers as a fine grey line along the base seals despite the suite’s filtration.",
